rComments: A very nice professor who genuinely cares about her students, and is happy to take time out of her day to help students. Although she has a bit of an accent, you'll be used to it in a lecture or two. Tests are not too hard as her lectures cover pretty much everything. Study and do your readings and you'll definitely do great.

Prof Santos' lectures are filled with her caring attitude, passion for physiology, and of course a few of her quirky jokes or stories to keep us engaged. She usually plans out a LOT of slides for her lectures, but usually skips a bunch so don't get overwhelmed. She genuinely cares about her students and did a fine job for her first time teaching.
